{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: condition-eu_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Condition instance conforming to the ConditionEuCore
    profile. Each invocation represents one clinical problem or encounter
    diagnosis on the patient's record. Unlike condition-eps_fsh.twig, this
    template does not emit a sentinel FSH instance when condition data is
    absent — instead it always opens and closes an HTML row, leaving it empty
    when condition is null.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: ConditionEuCore
    Must-support elements covered:
      category (two: problem-list + encounter-diagnosis), code (with preferred
      text), onsetDateTime (or absent-reason), abatementDateTime, subject,
      asserter

  RELATIONSHIP TO condition-eps_fsh.twig
    Both templates share the active/inactive logic and the three-column HTML
    pattern. Key differences are documented in the comparison table below.

    ┌──────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────┬──────────────────────┐
    │ Aspect                           │ condition-eu (this)    │ condition-eps        │
    ├──────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
    │ Profile                          │ ConditionEuCore        │ ConditionOblEuEps    │
    │ Null test operator               │ is not null (inverse)  │ is null (strict)     │
    │ No-condition output              │ Empty HTML row only    │ Full sentinel FSH    │
    │ addHTML_tr() placement           │ Before {% if %}        │ Inside {% else %}    │
    │ addHTML_trend() placement        │ After {% endif %}      │ Inside {% else %}    │
    │ Categories emitted               │ Two                    │ One                  │
    │ condition.code structure         │ Array-or-object        │ Single object only   │
    │ preferred term override          │ Unconditionally when   │ Only if differs from │
    │                                  │ non-empty              │ .display             │
    │ clinicalStatus rule              │ Not emitted            │ Emitted              │
    │ abatementDateTime guard          │ end non-empty only     │ end + inactive both  │
    └──────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────┴──────────────────────┘

  HTML ROW PLACEMENT — UNCONDITIONAL OPEN / CLOSE
    Unlike condition-eps where the HTML row is opened and closed inside the
    `{% else %}` branch (so no row at all when condition is null), this template
    opens `addHTML_tr()` BEFORE the `{% if condition is not null %}` check and
    closes `addHTML_trend()` AFTER the `{% endif %}`. This means:
      - When condition is not null: a populated row is produced.
      - When condition is null: an empty `<tr></tr>` row is emitted to the
        HTML bag. Callers should be aware this produces a blank table row in
        the narrative and HTML output.

  NULL TEST — `is not null`
    `{% if condition is not null %}` is the strict non-null check. As in
    condition-eps, `null` and `empty` are distinct in Twig:
      - `is not null` → false only for PHP/Twig null values
      - `is not empty` → false for null, "", [], and 0
    The calling PHP code must pass a true PHP null to make this branch false.

  DUAL CATEGORY
    Two category rules are emitted for every condition, covering both the
    problem-list and encounter-diagnosis perspectives:
      * category = $condition-category#problem-list-item "Problem List Item"
      * category = $condition-category#encounter-diagnosis "Encounter Diagnosis"
    Note: both rules use `category` without a slice index. FSH treats a
    repeating element with multiple `*` rules as setting successive values.
    SUSHI should compile both into the `category` array correctly; however,
    using `category[+]` would be more explicit and unambiguous.

  CONDITION CODE — ARRAY-OR-OBJECT NORMALISATION
    `condition.code` may arrive as either a single coding object or an array
    of coding objects, depending on the data source (e.g. ISH vs direct
    mapping). The template normalises this with an array-index probe:
      {% if condition.code[0] is not empty %}
      {% set thisconditioncode = condition.code[0] %}   { # array path # }
      {% else %}
      {% set thisconditioncode = condition.code %}      { # scalar path # }
      {% endif %}
    The `thisconditioncode` local variable then provides a consistent
    `.system`, `.code`, `.display`, `.preferredTerm` interface regardless of
    which path was taken.

    Note: this differs from the normalisation approach described in the README
    (`variable[0] is iterable ? variable : [variable]`). This template checks
    whether `condition.code[0]` is non-empty rather than whether the structure
    is iterable, which works reliably for both arrays and non-array objects in
    the PHP/Twig context.

  PREFERRED TERM — UNCONDITIONAL OVERRIDE
    When `thisconditioncode.preferredTerm` is non-empty, it unconditionally
    replaces `thisconditioncode.display` as the `preferred` variable:
      {% set preferred = thisconditioncode.display %}
      {% if thisconditioncode.preferredTerm is not empty %}
      {% set preferred = thisconditioncode.preferredTerm %}
      {% endif %}
    This differs from condition-eps which adds a further guard
    (`display != preferredTerm`) to prevent redundant overriding.

  NO clinicalStatus RULE
    Unlike condition-eps, no `* clinicalStatus` FSH rule is emitted. The
    active/inactive state is reflected only in the HTML cell styling
    (gray vs normal) — it is not recorded in the FHIR resource itself.
    Callers requiring an explicit clinicalStatus on the Condition resource
    should use condition-eps instead, or add the rule directly.

  abatementDateTime GUARD — END ONLY, NOT INACTIVE
    `abatementDateTime` is emitted whenever `condition.end` is non-empty,
    regardless of whether the condition is currently inactive:
      {% if condition.end is not empty %}
      * abatementDateTime = "{{ condition.end }}"
      {% endif %}
    This differs from condition-eps which requires BOTH end to be non-empty
    AND the condition to be inactive before emitting abatementDateTime.

  THREE-COLUMN HTML TABLE (no HEAD)
    TD 1 — Condition display: gray when inactive, normal when active.
    TD 2 — Onset / period: absent-reason "?" or formatted date / date-range.
            hperiod accumulates the display string (same pattern as EPS).
    TD 3 — Status label: "inactive" (gray) or "active" (normal).
    %%HEAD%% is empty — no addHEAD_th calls are made.

  ASSERTER (conditional)
    Same pattern as condition-eps: Reference to a PractitionerRole by UUID
    when `asserter` is non-empty.

  NARRATIVE — BODY ROWS ONLY (Pattern 1)
    Only emitHTML() is flushed inside text.div. %%HEAD%% is empty.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                         │ Type     │ Description                                │
  ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                       │ string   │ Unique resource id.                        │
  │ patient.instanceid               │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.              │
  │ patient.name                     │ string   │ Full display name for the subject Ref.     │
  │ condition                        │ object?  │ null → empty HTML row, no FSH body.       │
  │                                  │          │ Non-null → full condition output.          │
  │   .active                        │ string   │   Activity string "SYYYY-MM-DD"; first     │
  │                                  │          │   char "1" = active, "0" = inactive.       │
  │   .code                          │ object   │   Single coding object OR array of coding  │
  │             or object[]          │          │   objects. Normalised via code[0] probe.   │
  │   [→ thisconditioncode]          │          │   Resolved to a single coding object with  │
  │     .system                      │ string   │   CodeSystem URI.                          │
  │     .code                        │ string   │   Condition concept code.                  │
  │     .display                     │ string   │   Default display text.                    │
  │     .preferredTerm               │ string?  │   Unconditional display override when      │
  │                                  │          │   non-empty.                               │
  │   .start                         │ string?  │   ISO 8601 onset date. When empty,        │
  │                                  │          │   data-absent-reason is emitted.           │
  │   .end                           │ string?  │   ISO 8601 abatement date. Emitted as     │
  │                                  │          │   abatementDateTime when non-empty         │
  │                                  │          │   (regardless of active state).            │
  │ asserter                         │ object?  │   Optional asserter.                       │
  │   .instancerole                  │ string   │   UUID of the PractitionerRole resource.   │
  │   .name                          │ string   │   Asserter display name.                   │
  └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $condition-category — problem-list-item, encounter-diagnosis
    Condition code system URI — caller-supplied via thisconditioncode.system

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2026-03-06
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Condition-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: ConditionEuCore
Title: "Condition (EU core)"
Description: "Condition"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ instanceid }}"

{#
  addHTML_tr() is called BEFORE the condition null check — the row is always
  opened regardless of whether condition data is present. When condition is
  null, an empty <tr></tr> row is produced. See file header for implications.
#}
{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{% if condition is not null %}
{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  CONDITION DATA PRESENT
  `is not null` is a strict non-null check. An empty array or empty string
  would not trigger this branch — the caller must pass true PHP null to
  produce an empty row (see HTML row placement note in file header).
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}

{#
  ── Pre-calculations ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  activeflag / inactive — same pattern as condition-eps.

  thisconditioncode — normalises condition.code to a single coding object
    regardless of whether the source data provides an array or a scalar:
      Array path : condition.code[0] when code[0] is non-empty
      Scalar path : condition.code itself otherwise
    All subsequent code references use thisconditioncode.* consistently.

  preferred — uses thisconditioncode.preferredTerm unconditionally when
    non-empty (no further check that it differs from .display, unlike EPS).
#}
{% set activeflag = condition.active | slice(0, 1) %} {# "1" = active, "0" = inactive #}
{% set inactive = activeflag == 0 %}

{# Array-or-object normalisation for condition.code #}
{% if condition.code[0] is not empty %}
{% set thisconditioncode = condition.code[0] %} {# array path — use first element #}
{% else %}
{% set thisconditioncode = condition.code %}    {# scalar path — use as-is #}
{% endif %}

{# Preferred term — unconditional override when non-empty #}
{% set preferred = thisconditioncode.display %}
{% if thisconditioncode.preferredTerm is not empty %}
{% set preferred = thisconditioncode.preferredTerm %}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Dual category ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Both problem-list and encounter-diagnosis categories are emitted.
  Both use plain `category` without slice indexing — SUSHI sets successive
  values in the array. Using category[+] would be more explicit.
#}
* category = $condition-category#problem-list-item "Problem List Item"
* category = $condition-category#encounter-diagnosis "Encounter Diagnosis"

{# Code: explicit [0] index — one coding per condition #}
* code.coding[0] = {{ thisconditioncode.system }}#{{ thisconditioncode.code }} "{{ thisconditioncode.display }}"
* code.text = "{{ preferred }}"

{#
  ── TD 1: condition name ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Gray for inactive; normal for active.
  Note: no clinicalStatus FSH rule is emitted here or anywhere in this
  template (differs from condition-eps which emits it co-located with TD 1).
#}
{% if inactive %}
{{ addHTML_tdgray(preferred) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td(preferred) }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 2: onset / period ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Same pattern as condition-eps except abatementDateTime guard:
    This template emits abatementDateTime when condition.end is non-empty,
    regardless of the active/inactive state.
    condition-eps additionally requires the condition to be inactive.
#}
{% if condition.start is empty %}
* onsetDateTime.extension.url = "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/data-absent-reason"
* onsetDateTime.extension.valueCode = #unknown
{{ addHTML_td("?") }}
{% else %}
* onsetDateTime = "{{ condition.start }}"
{% set hperiod = condition.start|date('d-M-Y') %}
{% if condition.end is not empty %}
* abatementDateTime = "{{ condition.end }}"        {# emitted for any end date regardless of active state #}
{% set hperiod = hperiod ~ " - " ~ condition.end|date('d-M-Y') %}
{% endif %}
{{ addHTML_tdnb(hperiod) -}}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 3: active / inactive label ───────────────────────────────────────────
  Same style logic as condition-eps.
#}
{% if inactive %}
{{ addHTML_tdgray("inactive") -}}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("active") }}
{% endif %}

{# Patient reference #}
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  ── Asserter (conditional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Same pattern as condition-eps.
#}
{% if asserter is not empty %}
* asserter = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ asserter.instancerole }}) "{{ asserter.name }}"
{% endif %}

{% endif %} {# condition is not null #}

{#
  addHTML_trend() is OUTSIDE the {% if %} block — the row is always closed
  here, even when condition is null (producing an empty <tr></tr> row).
#}
{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative — body rows only (Pattern 1) ─────────────────────────────
  emitHTML() only — no HEAD bag populated, %%HEAD%% is empty.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips">{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor — intentionally empty #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
